  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/5720760/" class="title-link">当我们谈论核电、转基因时，我们实际在谈什么理论</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-5720760"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/iamfeifei/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1730421-3.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/iamfeifei/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">feifei</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2012-12-30"
      class="main-meta">2012-12-30 22:13:41</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_5720760_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  这个书评只是个简单的内容介绍，对于书里面提到的问题，我并没有什么成熟的看法，但是我觉得这本书还是很需要向大家推介以下的。  这本书是讨论政府应如何管制风险事物的。所谓的风险事物，涵盖的范围包括核电、转基因食品、二氧化碳排放等，它们的特点是并不具有爆炸物、有毒...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/5720760/#comments">(1回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">2有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_5720760_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_5720760_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>

      
  



